observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct the:

Concerned officials to ensure timely submission of complete RPCPPE to the Office of the Auditor;

Municipal Accountant to avail of the one-time cleansing of PPE;

GSO to maintain complete duly accomplished updated PCs to record all procurement and disposals of PPEs so that a reconciliation between the PCs with the physical count can be made;

Municipal Accountant and the GSO to conduct periodic reconciliation of the accounting and property records with the physical count and make the necessary adjustments on any discrepancies noted, for accurate and fair presentation of PPE account balances in the financial statement;

Concerned officials to take appropriate actions and expedite the registration of the land in the name of the Municipality; and

The Municipal Accountant should take action to record, reconcile and make necessary adjustments in the books of accounts relative to the parcels of land owned by the municipality.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive (LCE) agreed to direct the MTO:

a)  To follow the posting guidelines of the Notice of Delinquencies and exert all practicable means to increase collection and reach the BLGF target;

To prepare a certified list of all real property tax delinquencies which remained uncollected and reasons for non-collection, and submit the same to the Sanggunian to request for assistance in the enforcement of collection remedies;

To intensify their “Pulong-pulong” campaign to encourage payment of tax dues and educate the taxpayers of the benefits of early payment and consequences of non-payment of taxes; and

Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Assessor to reconcile and cleanse their records with regards to taxable properties.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to direct the:
Inventory Committee to complete the physical count of PPEs and the concerned officials to ensure timely submission of complete RPCPPE to the Office of the Auditor;
GSO to maintain duly accomplished and updated PCs and accompanying ARE, to record all procurement, issuances and disposals of PPEs so that a reconciliation between the PCs with ledger cards and physical count can be made;
Municipal Accountant and the GSO to conduct periodic reconciliation of the accounting and property records with the physical count and make the necessary adjustments on any discrepancies noted, for accurate and fair presentation of PPE account balances in the financial statements;
Concerned officials to take appropriate actions and expedite land registration in the Municipality’s name.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer to undertake the following actions:
a. Review transactions from prior years, exhaust all available remedies to obtain supporting documentation, and promptly record long-standing reconciling items;
For current year and onwards, analyze and verify discrepancies/errors and other reconciling items immediately following the preparation of the monthly Bank Reconciliation Statement (BRS);
Prepare Journal Entry Vouchers (JEV) for necessary corrections and adjustments; and
Establish a systematic process for retaining necessary documents and ensure timely updates to subsidiary ledgers for Cash in Bank-Local Currency Cash Account (LCCA) to improve the reliability and accuracy of financial reporting.

observations.managementAction:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (LCE) direct the Municipal Accountant to: 

Review the previous years’ transactions, secure the documents supporting the prior years’ reconciling items and cause the immediate recording of the reconciling items particularly those which persisted in the BRS for a long period;

For current year and onwards, analyze and verify discrepancies/ errors and other reconciling items immediately after the preparation of the monthly BRS, and prepare JEV for corrections/ adjustments in the GL to present accurate balances of the cash in bank accounts;

Enroll all the Municipality’s accounts under the LBP weAccess facility for early viewing of transactions and to obtain copy/ies of bank statements; and

Submit to the Auditor the monthly BRS of various Cash in Bank-LCCA SL balances without BRS, and henceforth ensure that monthly BRS of all bank accounts are submitted to the Audit Team within the prescribed period pursuant to COA Circular No. 96-011 and Section 74 of P.D. No. 1445.

